Unit Number,Unit Title,Key Topics
Unit 1,The Dawn of Civilization,"Early human societies, Neolithic Revolution, Rise of cities"
Unit 2,Ancient Mesopotamia and the Fertile Crescent,"Sumerians, Akkadians, Babylonians, Assyrians, Code of Hammurabi"
Unit 3,Ancient Egypt,"Old, Middle, and New Kingdoms, Pyramids, Pharaohs, Egyptian Society and Religion"
Unit 4,The Indus Valley Civilization,"Harappan culture, Urban planning, Trade, Decline of the Indus Valley"
Unit 5,Ancient China,"Shang and Zhou Dynasties, Confucianism, Taoism, Qin and Han Dynasties"
Unit 6,Ancient Greece,"Minoan and Mycenaean Civilizations, Greek City-States, Democracy in Athens, Persian Wars, Golden Age of Athens, Alexander the Great"
Unit 7,Ancient Rome,"Roman Republic, Roman Empire, Pax Romana, Christianity, Fall of Rome"
Unit 8,Early American Civilizations,"Maya, Aztec, Inca, Social structures, Achievements in science and architecture"
Unit 9,Classical India,"Vedic Period, Maurya and Gupta Empires, Hinduism, Buddhism, Indian Achievements"
Unit 10,The Rise of Islam,"Life of Muhammad, Spread of Islam, Islamic Golden Age, Caliphates"